Caption:
What is Fibromyalgia ?
Fibromyalgia syndrome (FMS) is a chronic syndrome characterized by chronic fatigue and  widespread pain with specific tender areas.
Here are some of the most common symptoms of Fibromyalgia :
 😬 Low resistance to pain, tender points
 😬Chronic muscular and skeletal pain
 😬Muscle burn, twitching, tightness.
 😬Draining fatigue and tiredness
 😬Insomnia or poor sleep quality
 😬Depression, stress, anxiety
 😬Concentration and focus issues “fibro-fog”
 😬Headaches, migraines.
 😬Irritable Bowel Syndrome
 😬Increased Menstrual Cramps
 😬Chronic fatigue

Caption:
.PORTUGAL.PORTO.
⠀
My dears 💕
Let me begin by saying that my trip to Portugal was a much-needed change of pace. Despite living on an Tenerife -popular among tourists, I found myself craving the energy of a city, its pulse, and rhythm..
⠀
💡The constant thoughts of the future, where to live, what to do, how to earn money, can be overwhelming and escaping this whirlpool sometimes requires a change of environment..
⠀
💦All needed at last month - it’s a chance to recharge, update my system and reinstall the value program. Re- Evaluate what I have in a new way..
⠀
☀️My SUNDAO practice has been a lifeline for me, pulling me out of a state of instability all of the time.
It is a universal activator of strength and vital energy, serving as my personal doctor, psychotherapist, and friend. It helps me shed what is no longer needed and gather resources to move forward.
⠀
🎈Portugal, coupled with my practice, was the perfect combination. It allowed me to shift gears, unwind, and gain a fresh perspective on life. I have reevaluated my priorities and am ready and to move forward.
⠀
In the coming days, I will be posting a schedule of offline meetings in Puerto de la Cruz and an invitation to a free mini-course featuring simple and versatile morning exercises to activate the energy system for all ages and levels. It’s simple pleasant and it works!
⠀
🎀Among the places I visited, Porto and Baleal Beach stood out to me the most.
⠀
For those who have been to Portugal, what is your favorite place? I am already planning my return in the near future.
⠀

Caption:
Woche achtzehn des Jahres ist angebrochen und der Monat Mai steht vor der Tür 🚪.

Alle, die mir schon länger folgen, wissen es: Ich liebe es am Ende eines Monats nochmal zurückzublicken und mir zu notieren was im vergangenen Monat alles so los war. Außerdem schaue ich mir dabei meine Wünsche & Ziele an um sie nicht aus den Augen zu verlieren. Diese kleine Reflexionspraxis schenkt mir Ruhe & Klarheit und fühlt sich für mich ein bisschen wie ein "Cleanup im Kopf" an :).

🎁 Meine Einladung an dich: Nimm' dir auch ein paar Minuten Zeit um dir die folgende Frage zu deinem April zu beantworten:

❓️Wobei warst du im April im Flowgefühl, also so konzentriert bei einer Sache, dass du alles um dich herum vergessen hast?

➡️ Beantworte diese Fragen gern gedanklich für dich oder schreibe dir deine Antworten auf.

Und weil's so schön ist, habe ich noch eine Frage zu deinem Mai ;) Welche schönen und/oder besonderen Momente stehen bei dir im Mai an?

Ich freue mich auf einen Austausch dazu in den Kommentaren mit dir & wünsche dir einen bewussten und erfüllten Mai☀️.

Alles Liebe,
Isabel 🧘🏻‍♀️❤️

Caption:
Sich gezielt darauf zu konzentrieren wofür man dankbar ist, ist eine traditionelle meditative Übung, bei welcher es darum geht sich auf das "kleine Glück" zu besinnen und sich an den Schönheiten des Alltags zu erfreuen. 

Die Dankbarkeitsmeditation basiert darauf dir bewusst zu machen was gerade an diesem Moment, in dem du dir die Zeit zum meditieren nimmst, schön ist und wofür du an diesem Tag/ an deinem Körper/ in deiner Partnerschaft oder in einem von dir gewählten Themen- bzw. Lebensbereich dankbar bist.

Zum Abschluss dieser Meditationsart kannst du dich auch darin versuchen dankbar für alles was nicht so geklappt hat zu sein und dir die Erkenntnisse, die du dadurch gewonnen hast,  bewusst machen. So schenkst du dir Wertschätzung, auch wenn es mal nicht so gut läuft. ➡️ Sollte dir das noch nicht gelingen: Nicht schlimm, einfach immer wieder probieren bis es klappt :).

Was dir die Dankbarkeitsmeditation bringt? Gute Laune, Zufriedenheit & die Schärfung deines Blicks für das Schöne.

Wofür bist du heute dankbar? 

happy meditation,
Isabel 🧘🏻‍♀️❤️

.
.

Caption:
🧘‍♀️ Achtsamkeit bedeutet auch unserem täglichen Stress ein Schnippchen zu schlagen und ganz alltägliche Dinge bewusst & konzentriert zu tun.

⚡️Doch wir kennen es wohl alle: Statt bewusst bei einer Sache zu sein, denken wir an tausend andere Dinge, die wir noch erledigen, einkaufen, besprechen "müssen".

Für mehr Bewusstsein in deinem Alltag, kommt hier eine kleine Achtsamkeitsübung für dich:

👀 Schaue mal bewusst woanders hin. 

Zum Beispiel auf deinem Weg zur Arbeit. Richte deinen Blick dabei einfach mal zur Seite oder nach oben und statt immer die rechte Straßenseite zu nutzen, nutze die Linke und betrachte die Häuser, Bäume, Blumen, die deinen Weg streifen. Was siehst du aus deinem neuen Blickwinkel? Was fällt dir Neues auf, was du vorher noch nie wahrgenommen hast?

Berichte gern was du bewusst anders machen möchtest oder was du heute bewusst anders gemacht hast & wie diese Erfahrung für dich war. 

Und denk dran: "Übung macht den Meister" ;) 

Schön, dass es dich gibt.
Isabel 🧘‍♀️❤️

.
.
.

Caption: Tuto audio meditaci nejen pro sváteční čas jménem Mariánská pouť do nitra přijala Martina Melounová. Představuje čtyři krátké intenzivní meditace, vhodné jako spočinutí do všedních dní, které vás za pomoci slov a imaginace provedou měsíční krajinou čtyř ženských archetypů (Černá Madona, Marie Magdaléna, Panna Marie, Královna ze Sáby). Relaxační hudba dotváří atmosféru hrou na hang drum a podporuje klesání dolů, do těla, do srdce, do lůna, do Matky Země, ke kořenům, kde můžete zažít pocit propojení a jednoty. Martina Melounová je lektorkou jógy, učitelkou angličtiny,  překladatelkou a pořadatelkou seminářů zaměřených na ženské zdraví a plodnost. Celková délka nahrávky je 42 minut a velikost souboru ke stažení 83 MB. Caption:
Aktive Meditationen zeichnen sich durch Bewegung aus. Meist konzentriert man sich dabei aufmerksam auf eine bestimmte Handlung, zum Beispiel auf das Gehen. 

Zu den aktiven Meditationsübungen zählen  beispielsweise auch die Zählmeditation, die Essmeditation oder das Singen von bestimmten Silben (= Mantren).

Das Gegenteil der aktiven Meditation ist die passive Meditation.

Hast du schon mal eine Aktive Meditation gemacht? Wenn ja, welche? 

happy meditation,

Caption:
✨Madre Tierra warmly welcomes you to a serene and transformative experience: “Deep Rebirth”, an intimate Ra-pé ceremony, complemented by a guided audio journey. This exclusive gathering, limited to just six participants, and offers a unique opportunity for personal renewal and spiritual awakening.✨

💕Embark on a profound voyage to explore the depths of your being, guided by the ancient wisdom plants via our fresh Ra-pé blends, sourced directly from the Peruvian Amazon, and the power of meditative audio. This experience is designed for all, inviting you to shed the old and embrace a new self, reborn with purpose and clarity.🍃

💚Ra-pé is a sacred herbal blend used in traditional indigenous ceremonies, primarily in the Amazon. This potent powder is administered through the nostrils, offering a profound spiritual cleansing. It is revered for its ability to ground participants, clear mental and physical blockages, and for reconnecting with the earth's energy. A tool for meditation and introspection, Ra-pé facilitates a journey towards inner balance and harmony.💚

“Deep Rebirth” promises a journey of enlightenment and purification:
🪶Discover the essence of what truly matters to you
🪶Let go of the burdens that no longer serve you
🪶Release past sorrows, hurts, and regrets
🪶Celebrate your joys, achievements, and successes
🪶Purify your being, unveiling the naked truth of your soul.
🪶Emerge renewed, ready to embody your truest self, with open arms to the future that awaits.

📍 Join us at Madre Tierra Shop, nestled in the serene Bang-Tao, Phuket, for this sacred assembly.
🕐 Time: 6:00 PM to 7:30 PM. Attendance is by booking.
For more information on availability and exchange, please connect with us directly 💌.

Caption:
This week’s “Meditation Yoga & Stuff with Sunita” Podcast Episode 144 is “Meditation On The Gap Between Thoughts”

Let’s delve into the serene realm of the mind’s silence—the gap between thoughts or ‘Antar Mauna’ in Sanskrit. In this tranquil journey, we navigate through the profound stillness that lies within every breath, uncovering the essence of mindfulness and inner peace. Discover the transformative power of acknowledging the pauses between thoughts, where serenity resides amidst life’s constant chatter. Through guided meditation and insightful discussions, we learn to embrace this sacred space as a gateway to self-discovery, clarity, and profound presence. Explore practical techniques and ancient wisdom from the realms of yoga and meditation, as Sunita gracefully illuminates the path towards inner harmony and mental clarity. Tune in to reconnect with your inner sanctuary, finding solace in the gentle rhythm of your breath, and embracing the timeless wisdom of the present moment.
Let’s explore techniques to embrace this meditative space and cultivate a deeper connection with our inner selves. Tune in for a journey of mindfulness and peaceful reflection. 
Link in Bio 🌸🙏🏼

Caption:
Woche neun des Jahres und der Monat März ist angebrochen. Ich liebe es am Ende eines Monats nochmal zurückzublicken und mir zu notieren was im vergangenen Monat alles so los war. Außerdem schaue ich mir meine Ziele an um sie nicht aus den Augen zu verlieren. Das schenkt mir Ruhe & Klarheit und fühlt sich für mich wie ein "Ceanup  im Kopf" an ;). 

Meine Einladung an dich: Nimm' dir ein paar Minuten Zeit um dir die folgenden zwei Fragen zu deinem Februar zu beantworten:

➡️ Was hat dir im Februar Energie geschenkt?

➡️ Was möchtest du im März sein lassen, weil es dir im Februar Energie raubt?

Beantworte diese Fragen gern gedanklich für dich oder schreibe dir deine Antworten auf. Natürlich freue ich mich auch auf einen Austausch in den Kommentaren mit dir ♡.

Ich wünsche dir einen bewussten und erfüllten März.

Alles Liebe,
Isabel 🧘🏻‍♀️❤️

Caption:
Höher, schneller, weiter. Harder, better, faster, stronger ... Es ist so leicht, sich in diesem Strudel zu verlieren, im Geschwindigkeitsrausch und Selbsoptimierungswahn. Zumal in dieser viel zitierten schnelllebigen Welt. 
Viele, die zwar wissen, dass ihr Nervensystem überlastet ist und etwas tun wollen, suchen dann den Shortcut zur Entspannung. Aber damit erwarten sie wieder, dass es schnell gehen soll. Viele haben vergessen, wie das geht, mal langsam zu machen. Mir fällt das auch nicht immer leicht … dabei ist es so wichtig. Für dein Nervensystem, für deinen Körper, für deine Seele 🙏

Es überrascht daher auch nicht, dass Meditation vielen Menschen heute schwer fällt. Weil sie meistens kein Shortcut ist, sondern ein Prozess, der nicht von heute auf morgen abgeschlossen ist. Und weil das, was man findet, hört und versteht, wenn man still und langsam wird, nicht immer angenehm ist und auch nicht immer sofort klar und eindeutig zu entziffern. 
Aber wenn du dich wirklich kennenlernen willst, dann führt kein Weg daran vorbei, still zu werden und zuzuhören. Und glaub mir: Es lohnt sich 🎉

Bist du bereit, das auszuprobieren? Traust du dich? Dann mach den Schritt und spring! 🤸‍♀️
Mein Deep Dive Meditation Kurs führt dich Schritt für Schritt in die Meditation ein und dich dabei unterstützen, dich besser kennenzulernen 🧘‍♂️🧘‍♀️

Caption:
🌞🎧 𝗻𝗲𝘂𝗲 𝗽𝗼𝗱𝗰𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝗽𝗶𝘀𝗼𝗱𝗲: #𝟭𝟭 - 𝗱𝗶𝗲 𝘄𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗼𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗻𝘄𝗲𝗻𝗱𝗲.

…vielleicht kennst du das auch: Ich hab lange sehr mit allen kirchlichen Bräuchen gehadert und mir echt schwer getan damit. Doch als ich begann mehr über alte Jahreskreisfeste zu lernen und zu begreifen, dass all diese Feste ein Äquivalent zu den ursprünglichen Bräuchen und Festen der Menschen sind, die im Einklang mit der Natur lebten - da hat sich für mich ein großer Frieden und ein tiefes Verständnis geöffnet.

So kann ich heute, wenn ich zB. ein Weihnachtslied höre, wo gesungen wird „all the angels sing, glory to the new born king“ - dann kann ich in meinem Herzen fühlen, was in der Essenz gemeint ist. Weil ich all die Menschen fühlen kann, die damals (ohne Strom & künstliches Licht) die Rückkehr des Sonnen-Kindes feierten 🌞💛. Und auch wenn wir heute all diese Annehmlichkeiten der Zivilisation genießen, so spüren wir trotzdem noch, wie kurz und dunkel die Tage sind....

🎧✨ die Podcast-Folge zur Wintersonnenwende startet mit ein paar einführenden Worten zu den alten Jahreskreisfesten & den Parallelen zwischen dem christlichen Weihnachtsfest und der Wintersonnenwende.

🧘 Danach wartet eine geführte Meditation (ca. 30 Minuten) auf dich. Mach es dir bequem und lass dich von meinen Worten begleiten: in ein Landen im Moment, in eine Atem-Beobachtung & schließlich in ein Hineinsinken in die Stille nach dem Aus-Atem. die Atemleere. in den Moment der Dunkelheit und Stille. und in eine Atem-Beobachtung, die dich mit dem Kreislauf des Lebens verbindet - der durch deinen Atem, in jedem Moment auch in dir spürbar wird.

Eine erdende und nährende Meditation, die du nicht nur zur Wintersonnenwende üben kannst - sondern zu jedem Zeitpunkt, in dem du dich hineinsinken lassen magst, in deinen Körper & deinen Atem. 💫

Happy listening & eine sanft-kraftvolle solstice-season!

LOVE,
Helene

#jahreskreis #wintersonnenwende #jahreskreisfeste #audiomeditation
Hashtags: audiomeditation, wintersonnenwende, jahreskreis, jahreskreisfeste

Caption:
Eine Freundin, die noch noch nicht so häufig meditiert hat, hat mich letzte Woche gefragt ob sie ihre Hände beim Meditieren  unbedingt zu einer bestimmten Stellung (einem Mudra) formen muss? 🤔

👌 Nein! Natürlich nicht ;). Du kannst deine Hände beim Meditieren auch in deinen Schoß oder auf deine Beine legen. Einfach so wie es für dich am bequemsten ist. 

🧘‍♂️ Außerdem musst du auch nicht im Schneidersitz meditieren. Es geht auch wunderbar im Sitzen, Liegen, Gehen oder Stehen:) 

😌 Und was auch kein Muss ist: Geschlossene Augen beim Meditieren. Wenn es sich für dich besser anfühlt, kannst du sie auch geöffnet lassen und dir wenn du magst einen Punkt suchen, den du während deiner Meditation fokussierst.

Du siehst Meditieren ist ganz individuell. Wichtig dabei ist nur, dass du dich wohl fühlst und dadurch dranbleibst 🧘🏻‍♀️❤️🧘‍♂️.

Welche Fragen zum Meditieren hast du?

Ich wünsche dir erholsame Meditationsauszeiten. 

Alles Liebe für dich 
Isabel 🧘🏻‍♀️❤️
.
.
.

Caption:
Ich liebe Leuchttürme. Das Leuchtturmlicht im Dunkeln zu sehen und zu sehen mit welcher Regelmäßigkeit es sich dreht und die Gegend zum Leuchten bringt, fasziniert und entspannt mich ❤️. 

Sowie das Leuchten des Leuchtturmlichts ganze Gegenden im Dunkeln erhellt, erhellt es mich in herausfordernden Zeiten, wenn Ich weiß was mich zum Leuchten bringt. 

💡Daher mein Tipp: Mach'dir eine Liste mit Dingen, die dich zum Leuchten bringen (entweder mit Zettel und Stift oder in deine Notizapp) und hole dir deine Liste hervor wann immer du sie gerade brauchst. 

❓️Was bringt dich zum Leuchten? Lass uns gern in den Kommentaren dazu austauschen und gegenseitig inspirieren.

Schön, dass es dich gibt ❤️.
Isabel 🧘🏻‍♀️
.
.
.

Letzte Woche war ich zum ersten Mal beim Lachyoga. Endlich. Nachdem ich es schon vor Jahren mal ausprobieren wollte & irgendwie immer was dazwischen kam. 

Wie ichs fand? Lustig 😃.

Was es bringt? Lachen setzt Endorphine, also Glückshormone frei, reduziert Stress, stärkt das Immunsystem, löst Verspannungen & wirkt sich positiv auf dein Wohlbefinden aus. Und das sind noch lang nicht alle positiven Wirkungen :). Dabei ist es egal ob es ein natürliches oder künstlich erzeugtes Lachen ist 😃 .

Was ich gelernt hab? Dass es ein Lachtelefon gibt :). Hier kannst du täglich von 9-21 Uhr anrufen & für 3 Minuten mit einem ehrenamtlichen Mitglied der Hotline zusammen lachen. Probiers doch mal aus 😃.

Und jetzt: Beliebigen Timer stellen & einfach mal so lachen oder das Lachtelefon anrufen und zusammen lachen unter der neuen Nummer 05031 5194380 (auf der Visitenkarte im Post ist noch die alte Nummer zu sehen). Weitere Infos gibts hier https://lachtelefon.de/ :)).

Alles Liebe für dich
Isabel 💛
.
.
.

Caption:
35 things you didn’t know about me for my 35th birthday…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I started my weight loss journey in late 2018 to shed the pounds and lost 70 pounds in the process.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now, it’s not only about physical health and fitness, but also the mental and emotional health of exercising as a lifestyle.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I can’t tell you how much I appreciate exercising to keep my mental and emotional health in check.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And that has led me to eating healthier, taking more time outside to get some vitamin D, and taking care of myself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Something my late father never did.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It’s okay to take small steps to take care of yourself to live a long life, and exercising has turned into the biggest small step I’m grateful for every single day.

Simple Morning Prayer Routine 🫶🏽
☕️Make Coffee 
🙏🏽 Pray Rosary 
😅 Daily Examen

📖 Bible Chapter
✍🏽 Optional: Morning Writing
.

📚 Spiritual Reading
📖 Bible Chapter
🙏🏽 Novenas/ Divine Mercy/ Other Prayers
🤫 10 Min Silence (Meditation)
✍🏽 Optional: Afternoon Writing
.
Simple Evening Prayer Routine:
👩🏽‍❤️‍👨🏿 Evening Couples Rosary 
🎧 Word on Fire Institute Audio
😅Optional: Daily Examen
.
Modifications: all prayer, spiritual reading, Examens, etc can be done via audio nowadays, so implementing while commuting, dog walking, cooking, washing dishes, showering, going potty, cleaning the house … is a great way to fit in what you need spiritually each day even when you think you don’t have the time 🥰 Also, encouraging your kids, puppy, your Beloved to join you in any of these is not only a great way to pray together but sets the tone of routine, calmness, and much needed serenity for everyone in the house 😍 YOU set the vibe - from the top down, everyone else falls in line according to what we do in our daily routines and needs met. 
*** 💁🏽‍♀️ProTip #1: Seaside Jazz Music | Outdoor Cafe on YouTube is my jam in the background when soaking up reading, writing and scripture 🌊🎶 
*** 💃🏽🎤 ProTip #2: Praise & Worship in your living room for 10 minutes with the lyrics on your TV is an excellent way to open the day! Try it out 🫶🏽 #GodFirst #PuppyPrayerTime #CoffeeAndPrayer #DailyRoutines #ChooseToBloom #Bloomified 🌺

Caption:
🌿

Ukończyłam pierwszą medytację dynamiczną w formie audio 🥰🎼 (przewiń kafle, żeby osłuchać fragment). Wcześniej miałam okazję prowadzić takie sesje na żywo.

Dziękuję za Wasz feedback ☺️ wiem, że będę tworzyć ich dużo bo czuję to całą sobą i przede wszystkim sam proces tworzenia (od pisania, nagrania po montaż zajmujący kilkanaście godzin) jest dla mnie samej wielką medytacją💆🏼‍♀️

Dlaczego medytacja dynamiczna/programowanie umysłu? 

🫠pracujesz w niej ze swoją wyobraźnią i aktywnie tworzysz obrazy w swoim umyśle- ja tu pełnię rolę przewodnika i Cię kieruję, a wszystko robisz Ty sam/a. Tylko Ty masz dostęp i wpływ na swój umysł i to się dzieję dla Twojego dobrostanu 
🫠wykorzystujesz głęboką relaksację i działanie 1 z 6-ciu fal występujących w naszym 🧠- fali alfa. Podczas działania tej fali Twój umysł szybciej chłonie wspierające sugestie 
🫠z moim prowadzeniem schodzisz w stan głębokiego relaksu, na poziom 0 i tam karmisz swoją podświadomość wspierającymi autosugestiami, które tylko i wyłącznie działają na Twoją korzyść i rozwój 

Medytacja jest napisana pod przekonania- transformację na te wspierające i budujące. Poparta jest również zakotwiczeniem wpierających Cię wzorców i działań, aby przyspieszyć realizację Twoich pragnień 😀📈

Nasza wyobraźnia ma nieocenioną moc i właśnie w tej medytacji to wykorzystujemy. Każda wpierająca sugestia wpływa na Ciebie długo potem- nie tylko w trakcie odsłuchiwania medytacji. Buduje nowe ścieżki neuronowe w Twoim umyśle, wpływa na neuroplastyczność Twojego umysłu i pracuje, otwiera się w Tobie długo potem.

W skrócie: zdrowy, odżywczy pokarm dla Ciebie i Twojego 🧠🥰

Możesz po nią sięgać jak tylko potrzebujesz. Jeżeli masz ochotę zatopić się w niej to inwestycja w siebie, swój relaks i miód na umysł to 50 zł 👌

Napisz do mnie, z ogromną chęcią się nią podzielę ❤️

Caption:
🫠🙇🏼‍♀️

W tym pięknym miejscu, w spokoju i jasnych myślach skończyłam swoją pierwszą medytację dynamiczną w formie audio 🥰🎼 (przewiń kafle, żeby osłuchać fragment)

Dziękuję za piękny feedback i pochwały mego głosu 😀 też to czuję 😉 ahh będę tworzyć ich duuużo bo czuję to całą sobą i przede wszystkim sam proces tworzenia (od pisania, nagrania po montaż zajmujący kilkadziesiąt godzin) jest dla mnie samej wielką medytacją💆🏼‍♀️

Dlaczego medytacja dynamiczna/programowanie umysłu? 

🫠pracujesz w niej ze swoją wyobraźnią i aktywnie tworzysz piękne obrazy w swoim umyśle- ja tu pełnię rolę przewodnika i Cię kieruję, a wszystko robisz Ty sam/a. Tylko Ty masz dostęp i wpływ na swój umysł i to się dzieję dla Twojego dobrostanu 
🫠wykorzystujesz głęboką relaksację i działanie 1 z 6-ciu fal występujących w naszym 🧠- fali alfa. Podczas działania tej fali Twój umysł szybciej chłonie wspierające sugestie 
🫠z moim prowadzeniem schodzisz w stan głębokiego relaksu, na poziom 0 i tam karmisz swoją podświadomość wspierającymi autosugestiami, które tylko i wyłącznie działają na Twoją korzyść i rozwój 

Medytacja jest napisana pod przekonania- transformację na te wspierające i budujące. Poparta jest również zakotwiczeniem wpierających Cię wzorców i działań, coby przyspieszyć realizację Twoich pragnień 😀📈

Nasza wyobraźnia ma nieocenioną moc i właśnie w tej medytacji to wykorzystujemy. Każda wpierająca sugestia wpływa na Ciebie długo potem- nie tylko w trakcie odsłuchiwania medytacji. Buduje nowe ścieżki neuronowe w Twoim umyśle, wpływa na neuroplastyczność Twojego umysłu i pracuje, otwiera się w Tobie długo potem.

W skrócie: zdrowy, odżywczy pokarm dla Ciebie i Twojego 🧠🥰

Możesz po nią sięgać jak tylko potrzebujesz. Jeżeli masz ochotę zatopić się w niej to inwestycja w siebie, swój relaks i miód na umysł to 50 zł 👌

Napisz do mnie, z ogromną chęcią się nią podzielę bo jest w tym wielka wartość i kawał mojego serducha ❤️

Ściskam 😁☀️
.

Caption:
Mein Ort der Ruhe und Entspannung. 🙏

Nachdem wir zuhause seit Monaten von morgens bis nachmittags Baulärm zu hören bekommen und zusätzlich seit einigen Tagen die Gärtner draußen um die Häuser die Grünflächen  mähen und Hecken schneiden, war es soooo angenehm, heute Vormittags an meinem Lieblingsort zu sitzen, den Enten 🦆und anderen Wasservögeln, dem Zwitschern der Vögel🐦‍⬛ in den Bäumen🌳 und Sträuchern 🌿zuzuhören, die Augen zu schließen und direkt in die Meditation zu gleiten.🙏

Caption:
Una dedicatoria:
“Hablo de piedras que siempre se han acostado al raso o que han dormido en su yacimiento y en la noche de las vetas. No interesan a la arqueología, ni al artista, ni al diamantista. Nadie hizo con ellas palacios, estatuas, joyas; ni siquiera diques, fortificaciones o tumbas. 

No son útiles ni falsas. Sus facetas no brillan en ninguna sortija, en ninguna diadema. No promulgan, guardadas en caracteres indelebles, las listas de victorias, las leyes del imperio. Ni hitos, ni estelas. Expuestas a la intemperie, aunque sin honores ni reverencias, solo dan testimonio de sí mismas.” 

¿Pero de qué te estoy hablando? 
De Rogelio Guijarros y su libro de piedras. 

Las fotos son de la salida que hicimos el otro día al Geominero. 

Si quieres leer más, o dibujar mas, con las audioguias y las piedras virtuales del #clubdepiedras

Caption:
There is still time to join our Summer Audio Meditation Series!! 

Let rest be your medicine for a healthful summer and the foundation of your self-care practices.

Weekly series that ends September 5th 

Amid the heat and activity of the summer months, reserve time for quiet, stillness, and rest. In this season of growth, consider yourself and your inner landscape a garden. Practicing stillness allows us the opportunity to listen deeply to our internal dialogue and become the observer fully engaged and present in our lives. What would we like to grow and nurture this season? Rest is an essential ingredient for our health and wellness as human beings, taking a respite from doing, and allowing what is true for us to arise.

Details:
•The Summer Siesta Recorded Weekly Meditation Series is offered by Judy Bousquin through Yoga Moves
•This weekly series begins July 11 and sojourns through September 5
•Investment in yourself and your meditation practice: $29
•All meditations are original creations that are downloaded onto your favorite device to listen whenever and how often you want to practice
•No experience is necessary; seasoned and new meditators welcome

Each week you will receive:
•One guided meditation
•One silent meditation with a prompt
•One poem
•A writing prompt
•Resources when available

Your meditations will arrive weekly in your email inbox from Judy
at healingandrenewal@gmail.com, the morning of the expected date, each Tuesday between 7/11 – 9/5/2023

You will have ongoing access to your teacher, Judy Bousquin
As these meditations are recorded, take your practice wherever you go. For questions, reach out to Judy through yogamoves02180@gmail.com with Summer Meditation Series in the subject line.

Caption:
Meditation has been shown to be effective in reducing anxiety for a number of reasons. Here are some of the ways in which meditation can help an anxious mind:
🌸Calming the nervous system: Anxiety is often accompanied by physical symptoms such as rapid breathing, increased heart rate, and muscle tension. Meditation can help to calm the nervous system, reducing these physical symptoms and promoting a sense of relaxation and calm.
🌸Focusing the mind: An anxious mind is often characterized by racing thoughts and a sense of overwhelm. Meditation can help to quiet the mind and bring focus to the present moment, reducing feelings of stress and anxiety.
🌸Developing awareness: Meditation can help to develop an awareness of our thoughts and emotions, allowing us to observe them without judgment or reaction. This can help to reduce the intensity of anxious thoughts and feelings and promote a sense of peace and equanimity.
🌸Building resilience: Regular meditation practice can help to build resilience and coping skills, making it easier to navigate stressful situations and manage anxiety in the long term.

Caption:
O poder do: "Eu sinto muito, me perdoe, eu te amo, sou grato."

Esta frase é simples, mas poderosa. Você pode repeti-la para si mesmo sempre que se sentir sobrecarregado com emoções negativas ou pensamentos limitantes.

Ao dizer "Eu sinto muito", você está expressando tristeza e arrependimento pelos seus pensamentos ou ações negativas. 

Ao dizer "Me perdoe", você está pedindo perdão a si mesmo e aos outros por quaisquer erros que tenha cometido. 

"Eu te amo" é uma afirmação de amor incondicional para si mesmo e para os outros. 

E "Sou grato" é uma expressão de gratidão pela oportunidade de crescer e aprender com suas experiências.

Mude sua vida... 🍀🍀🍀

Caption:
• METTA MEDITATION •⁣
⁣
Die Metta Meditation ist ein kraftvolles Werkzeug, um Liebe und Mitgefühl in Dir selbst zu entwickeln und es mit anderen zu teilen. ⁣
Sie beginnt damit, dass wir uns selbst lieben und freundlich behandeln, damit wir diese Energie nach außen strahlen und sie an die Menschen um uns herum weitergeben können.⁣
⁣
Diese Meditation praktiziere ich seit vielen Jahren und bin so dankbar für diese wundervolle Energie. Darum habe ich die Audio-Journey entwickelt, die eine geführte Metta Meditation (mp3), eine digitale Affirmationskarte sowie einen Journaling-Guide enthält.⁣
⁣
Mit dieser Journey kannst Du tief eintauchen und so viel Mitgefühl für Dich selbst und andere entwickeln. Du kannst alte Wunden heilen und über Dich und Deine menschliche, weltliche Erfahrung hinaus wachsen.⁣
⁣
Es ist pure Magie!⁣
⁣
Kennst Du die Praxis?⁣
Teile Deine Gedanken, Erfahrungen und Fragen so gern in den Kommentaren.⁣
⁣
Die Journey findest Du im Link in meiner Bio.⁣
⁣
Liebe zur Dir.⁣
Deine Kasia ✌🏻⁣
⁣

Our next project works on the same principle. @wello.in is an audio meditation and healing mobile application where users can indulge in social community in the app itself. Caption:
🥰🎤 ABOUT YESTERDAY... 🎤🥰
Yes Yes Yes!!
Die Vibe, waarin je voelt dat het dichter en dichter komt.
Steeds maar concreter wordt!
Waaw, ik kan er zo erg van genieten. 😍

Ik voelde me helemaal in mijn nopjes gisteren en als een visje in het water met die micro voor m'n neus.
En dat ook absoluut door de aanwezigheid en kundige begeleiding van Luk De Deckers, al vele jaren m'n partner in sunshine en crime voor heel veel muzikale projecten en samenwerkingen die we samen vorm mochten geven.

Gisteren, terwijl de regen op het dakraam boven ons viel en meer dan eens zorgde voor een noodzakelijke pauze onder het opnemen, werd mijn tekentafel even omgetoverd tot een opnametafel. 

En op Dinsdag 28 maart wordt de afgewerkte versie ervan doorgestuurd naar iedereen die zich aanmeldde voor de Dagboek-Challenge.
Het wordt een zalige reis en ontmoeting met jouw Innerlijke Vuurkracht.

Inschrijven voor deze unieke ervaring kan nog tot 17 maart, oftewel aanstaande vrijdag, via deze link: https://www.moonmoments.be/products/maandagboek-moonjournal-ram-21-03-tot-19-04

Heel erg welkom!

Fijne zaterdag, en veel maanliefs van me 🤍🌛🌝🌜
Floor xxx

Caption:
💫 I don’t take action unless I am in alignment. Unless it feels right. And sometimes I'm not. And sometimes, it doesn’t.  And sometimes, I don’t know what the next right step is. 

So I have to sit and wait. Sitting and waiting does not sit well with me. Both of them make me uncomfortable. 
Like I should be doing more. 
Or at least be doing something.

But what I am starting to realise is that when we are in a period of waiting, it’s so much more about being, and so much less about doing. 
Being in the moment. Being present. 
In the discomfort. 
In the listening. 
In the lesson. 
In the learning. 

And less about doing the action. 
About making it happen.  About moving forward.

Sometimes the best thing to do in these moments is just to sit. 
And rest. 
And listen. 
And be silent. 
And be still. 
And be present. 
And just be. 

Easier said than done, right? 
I know. Believe me, I know. 
But let’s try it together. 
If you’re in a season of waiting, let’s embrace the waiting.  Let’s stop worrying about what comes next and just enjoy what is right now. In front of you. 

Maybe instead of feeling uncomfortable, the waiting could feel like peace. Let it warms up to you. Let it come to you naturally. Perhaps, you might like it. You might warm up to it. It steadies the mind and shows you the paths ahead. And what needs to be done. 

Find your seat and sit in stillness. In silence. 💫🙏🏾

Caption:
As days grow shorter and autumn hues give way to winter greys in the Northern Hemisphere, this Sunday marks the dawn of a season of yearning that many Jesus-followers call Advent.

Long ago Mary began her long journey to Jerusalem with Joseph to oblige their state’s census while growing the life of Emmanuel (God-with-us) within her.

Now, we attend to life’s obligations while carrying hoped-for Divine deep within us, culminating in our collective celebration of the Christmas season.

But how do we move from life’s hidden gestation to birth?

Can we enter this season without spiritually disassociating?

Oftentimes, Advent is framed as a contest between ‘daybreak’ and ‘darkness,’ resisting the night to usher in the light. 

But perhaps the way we receive the blessings latent in this Advent season is not to chase away the darkness that we would hide, deny, & repress in ourselves and our current circumstances—but instead to embrace it.

Jung concurred, allegedly saying “What you resist, persists. What you embrace, dissolves.” 

The Messiah whose advent we first anticipated would grow from his nurture in Mary’s dark womb to being a counter-cultural figure with powerful guidance that bucked the prevailing wisdom of his day. While his own brother James would teach the conventional path of “resist the devil and he will flee from you,” Jesus advocated for embrace:

“Make friends with your Adversary quickly while you are together on the way, so your opponent may not hand you over to the judge, and the judge to the officer, and you be thrown into prison.” (Matt 5:25)

Can we cease demonizing the darkness?

Can we hold our shadows close this Advent? 

I’d like to try. And I’d like this effort to be beautiful. So I’ve teamed up with my dear friend and colleague @ourladyofperpetualbliss — a gifted poet, scholar and preacher—to give us a guided meditation we can immerse ourselves in, right now.

Jennifer invites us into the grand story of Incarnation —imaginally placing ourselves in the energies of Mother and Child. Please give yourself a few minutes to unite the Divine Darkness and Holy Light within yourself in this rich audio meditation, link in bio.

Caption:
We all feel stressed sometimes, but too much stress can have a negative impact on our physical and mental health.

Some common effects of stress are: 
🔸Headaches
🔸Muscle tension
🔸Fatigue
🔸Anxiety
🔸Feeling overwhelmed
🔸Sleep problems

Luckily, there are things we can do to manage stress, like journaling, moving our bodies, spending time with loved ones, getting out in nature, and meditating.

In honour of National Stress Awareness Day today, we invite you to download your free copy of Anxiety at Ease, Please. This short audio meditation was created by Cheryl to help calm an anxious mind and body. (Link in bio).

Caption:
Take a moment to stop and breathe.

Notice that when you struggle, strive, fight, reach, grasp or force your mind, you push away the peace you seek. 

And the moment you stop, soften the mind, relax your body, cease striving, and give up the struggle, the peace you seek is already here as a significant presence of an effortless being. 

The very nature of grace is effortless ease. It is already wholly complete, whole, free, vast, and open.

It intrinsically knows how to care for every aspect of your life and is always in flow.

Like a river flowing over water-smoothed rocks, it has a natural ease.

Yet it’s as if no one is doing the doing or ‘flowing the flow.’ It just is. 

It is simultaneously supremely restful and scintillatingly alive: it loves to give birth to creation. This flow knows the proper action in each moment.

Take a moment to stop and breathe today with the free audio meditation from Brandon. 

🎵 https://www.thejourney.com/the-journey-audio 🎵

Caption:
I’m SO excited about this launch! 

Creating a meditation package is something I’ve been wanting to do for MONTHS—and I finally got the courage to launch one. And I must say, it’s pretty damn good.🦋🤭✨

If you are new to meditation or want to create a more consistent mindfulness practice and increase your self-awareness, then this meditation challenge is for you!

The idea for this challenge came to be during a deep yoga session... and just a few weeks later, it was born! 

The challenge consists of 3 daily guided meditations (including breathing exercises) designed to help wake up, energize, and restore your body:

☀️ Morning — WAKE UP + GROUND
10-minute energy-boosting, grounding & balancing meditation to begin your day on an intentional and anxiety-free note.

✨ Afternoon — CHECK IN + CONNECT
10-minute energizing, focus-enhancing & stress relieving meditation to reconnect during the day.

🌙 Night — REST + REFLECT 
7-minute meditation to help you reflect, rest, and digest at the end of the day.

The goal is to complete these three meditations every day for at least 5 days (I recommend at least 2 weeks if you are new to meditating/breathwork and want to get in the habit of creating a consistent daily practice).

You can visit thebalancedsociety.podia.com to download the meditation pack OR visit the link in my bio 💫🌱

Caption: How is everyone doing? Ive been thinking about failure this week and how human beings perceive failure, often with great fear and trepidation but I believe it can wind up being a beautiful thing. It makes us wait longer and work on our ideas and the reasoning behind them. It helps us to mature. We don't live on a promise of a possible destination and the compass has a habit of altering course mid step. Work often takes years and years to get into production. This is why it is soo fundamentally important for us to really truly be in love with the thing. This is the story of how an eight minute film about a lonely satellite fix it guy took thirteen years to get made.\n\n#shortfilm #filmpodcast #audiomeditation #lostinspace #cosmicdrama

Caption:
8 cups of calm ☕️

In this practice, we connect to sound in an intentional way. In the full-length audio, I mention that we may have very different breathing rates so if we are not in sync, that is completely okay - hum at your pace without judgment. Also, if for any reason gently plugging the ears (lightly pressing on the tragus) feels triggering as the sound intensifies, unplug and practice with the ears open. If you’d like to get creative, let your voice and body play!

[one-minute-transcript: *chime* As you begin to settle into a space of ease, listen for a few moments to the sounds around you. Capture what you hear and let it be.
Now, create a few open-mouth exhales, shifting your attention to sounds made by your body. Now, we will add in another layer of sound by humming.]

Listen to this full audio and more on my website 📧 ᴏʟᴀᴄɪᴇᴢᴀᴋ.ᴄᴏᴍ (link in bio @yogatherapywithola). Sign up to receive my weekly 𝓪 𝓬𝓾𝓹 𝓸𝓯 𝓬𝓪𝓵𝓶 newsletter in your email inbox.

With love, Ola ♥

Caption:
7 cups of calm ☕️

This practice invites creativity. I am guiding you through a visualization practice that weaves components of loving-kindness and breathing with self-inquiry.

[one-minute-transcript: *chime* soften your shoulders. soften your jaw. soften your gaze. and maybe close your eyes. tune in to your body breathing. as you breathe, examine your state of being. from head to toe and toe to head. from the outside-in and the inside-out. what do you notice? if you were to share your answer as a color representation, what would you say?]

The benefits of sound meditation are immense. Here are some of the benefits of sound meditation 👇🏾:
1.	Quieting the mind.
2.	To empower cognitive change.
3.	To access and release trauma
4.	To fine-tune self-observation.
5.	Increasing self-confidence.

Caption:
“What the soul wants, what it hungers for, what it is spending time on this earth to achieve, is a fully conscious, bodily experience of the Present.”​​​​​​​​
― Philip Shepherd,​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
There’s no getting away from your body – but getting along with it can sometimes feel like managing a troubled marriage. And that’s understandable because we are taught to live in our heads, not our bodies.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
But the body harbours a deep resource of grounded, calm intelligence. Once you access that resource and learn to rest within it, you find yourself at peace in the present, and clear about your next step. Enjoy these eight embodied meditations by Philip to help you dive into wholeness. Each exercise is designed to take you on a different adventure into an exploration of wholeness.  This collection of audio recordings from Philip are meant to be listened to sequentially and are a perfect accompaniment to your exploration to wholeness. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Link in our BIO or via https://embodiedpresent.com/product/8-essential-meditations/​​​​​​​​

Caption:
Meditations from King Island

Nature does not hurry, yet everything is accomplished - L.Tzu

Hari Om Yogis.

We are pleased to release a series of meditations we have been working on whilst living in King Island.
Inspired by the environment, this NEW audio series is designed for you to develop a regular meditation practice.
Each meditation is a different journey inward where you will learn to calm your mind, steady your nervous system & develop a more integrated, peaceful and calm state of being.

In this series we teach you 5 unique meditation techniques.

1. Earth Meditation (15min):
Cultivate a sense of being anchored in one’s body and supported by life.
2. Concentrative Meditation (17min):
Create focus and awareness on one point – the breath, with mantra and the eyebrow centre.
3. Active Visualisation (15min):
Use the powers of our imagination to cultivate favourable situations.
4. Chakra Meditation (26min):
Using energy of the breath and mantra to awaken our physic centres.
5. Yoga Nidra (25min):
This is where we lie down and use our awareness to consciously relax the body.

We will supply you with a link that allows you to stream or download all 5 audio meditations to your device, so you can practice anytime!
The meditations have no expiry date and are yours to practice for years to come.

ALL YOURS FOR $95
http://www.hawthornyoga.com/content/meditations_from_king_island.asp

We hope that these meditations inspire you to practice regularly and to reap the many benefits of this wonderful practice called meditation.
Namaste
Jacqui & Shimon

Caption:
FOR MORE INFO CLICK ON LINK IN BIO. 

Dreams are not a separate occurrence in our life experience: What we do in the day connects with what we dream and what we dream connects to what we do in the day.  By bringing awareness to those processes we are able to fully enjoy this experience that naturally comes to us every night throughout our entire life.

PROGRAM:
 

 ✅WEEK 1: you will learn how to sleep better and how consciousness and mind influence our sleep and dreaming. 
 
 ✅WEEK 2: you will discover how to work during the day to influence your dreams
 
 ✅WEEK 3: continue the exploration of different level of consciousness and I will share with you tips on how to sleep and dream better.

 
The group is suitable for anyone who wants to draw attention to dreams and use them to shine a light into a certain area of their life: relationships, creativity, spirituality, material wealth, health and others. 

 Participation is voluntary and free. There is always the possibility to leave at any moment.

Give it a try, open up to your own dreams!

Caption:
2021թ.-ի վերջին մեդիտացիաս🧚։ Այս տարին իմ ինտուիցիան մեծ վերելք ապրեց ու փոխեց իմ կյանքը, ուստի որոշեցի մի շատ հավես պրակտիկայով կիսվեմ ձեր հետ, որը ձեզ նույնպես կօգնի ակտիվացնել ու հետագայում զարգացնել ձեր ինտուիցիան։
Իսկ գիտեք, թե որ օրգանն է պատասխանատու ինտուիցիայի համար? Շատերը կասեն սիրտը, բայց իրականում դա մեր կոնանման գեղձն է (шишковидная железа) կամ շատերի համար միստիկ 3-րդ աչք ասվածը։ Երբ այն ակտիվ է, մենք սկսում ենք մեր սրտի հուշումները ճիշտ հասկանալ։ 
Այնպես որ, եթե իմ գրածը մի փոքր կպավ ձեր սրտին ու հավատում եք ձեր ձեռքերի ուժին 🙌, ապա մի վարանեք ու գրեք ինձ։ Մեդիտացիան սիրով ձեզ է սպասում 💚
Որպես էներգափոխանակում կխնդրեմ սրտիկել ու հնարավորության դեպքում կիսվել գրառումով, իսկ ցանկության դեպքում հանգանակել։ Որովհետև կյանքում ամենինչ փոխադարձ պետք է լինի, աստվածային օրենքն այդպես է աշխատում 😊

Caption:
💚 Իմ խոստացած առաջին մեդիտացիան արդեն պատրաստ է ու նվիրված է սրտին: Ինչպես կյանքում, այնպես էլ էներգետիկ պլանում ամենակարևոր կենտրոնը՝ չակրան, սրտի կենտրոնն է: 
✔️Եթե ցանկանում ես մուտք գործել ինքնաճանաչման ու այսպես ասած հոգևոր, էզոտերիկ դաշտ, ուրեմն կարևոր է սկսել հենց սրտից: Քանի որ նա երկրայինի ու երկնայինի մեջտեղում է, նրանց միացնողն ու բալանսավորողը: Եթե սիրտդ բաց է, ուրեմն մնացած բոլոր հարցերն արդեն լուծելի են, քանի որ այդ հարցերին սկսում ես նայել ոչ թե ուղեղով, այլ սրտով, իսկ սիրտը երբեք չի խաբում, պարզապես պետք է սովորել լսել նրան✨
Հաճախ սրտի, սիրո մասին խոսելիս մենք պատկերացնում ենք վարդագույն, գուցե ոմանք կարմիր գույները, բայց էներգետիկ պլանում այն կանաչ գույնի է 🤗
🔥Այսպիսով առաջին քայլն արված է սիրելիներս Ձեր սրտի բացման համար և այն ձեզանից շատ քիչ ժամանակ կխլի ընդամենը 10 րոպե։ 
 Խնդրում եմ խիստ չդատել ձայնագրության ու տեխնիկական հարցերի հետ կապված: Բոլոր թերությունները ժամանակի ընթացքում ուղղելի են: Ինձ համար կարևորը ձեր ստացածի արդյունքն է ու արձագանքը☺️ Քանի որ ձեր հետադարձ կապից է կախված շարունակությունը: 

❗Ցանկացողները գրեն ինձ անձնական նամակ:

💚Կրկին հիշեցնեմ, որ մեդիտացիաները հանգանակությամբ են ըստ ցանկության կամ պարզապես շնորհակալություն ի սրտե:

Ձեր Հռիփսիմե🧚

Caption:
🎶Áudio Medita Comigo LovePair🐾 - Desafio 21 dias 

No dia 11/11 , criei uma meditação áudio para me conectar ainda mais com a Mia, com a Sasha, com a Dama e com o Lucky. Nesta meditação guiada vamos visualizar saúde, amor, felicidade, paz para eles e refletir e sentir o quão eles são importantes para nós.

Desde que me lembro que gravava coisas com a minha voz e ouvia. Em miúda gravava num gravador a pilhas que tinha um microfone incorporado 🎤, mais tarde gravava no iPod poemas de Português ou resumos/matéria que tinha que decorar para os testes no secundário. Depois passei a gravar áudios no WhatsApp ou no gravador do telemóvel.
A audição é um dos sentidos que tenho mais apurado. E que jeito me deu durante aquele tempo todo em que tive de descansar a minha visão. Durante esse tempo ouvi muitas medições em áudio (e ainda oiço) e muita música.

Este áudio - meditação 🧘 tem apenas 8 minutos , e durante os próximos 21 dias vamos ouvi-lo todos os dias e dedicar este tempo a nós 💞 e aos nossos animais.

Queres juntar-te a mim e ter acesso a esta meditação gravada para te conectares e meditares com o teu animal de estimação? Envia-me uma mensagem privada para saber mais.

Com amor,
Joana Soares

Caption: Through my yoga teacher training I was made to understand something I already had known of. Caption:
Հիմա կասեք էս ինչա ասում))) Այո շատերի համար նորը, ովքեր չգիտեն իմ նախասիրությունների և վերջին 3 տարին իմ կյանքի անբաժան մասը կազմող յոգայի ու մեդիտացիոն պրակտիկաների մասին🧘։ Մի նոր փուլ իմ կյանքում, որը փոխեց իմ աշխարհայացքն ու ընկալումը։ Մի նոր փուլ, որը բերեց ինձ իմ իսկական էությանը🧚։
Իսկ հիմա զգում եմ եկել է ժամանակը ձեր հետ կիսվելու իմ փորձի ու գիտելիքների մասին։ Երկար էի մտածում, բայց ինչպես.... ու մի սիրուն օր միտք ծագեց հայերեն լեզվով մեդիտացիաներ ձայնագրել։  Այո, դու ճիշտ ես կարդում, մեդիտացիա` իմ ձայնով ու իմ էներգիայով լցված 💚
Քանի որ ճաշակներն ու նախասիրությունները տարբեր են ու հնարավոր չէ ստեղծել այնպիսի մի բան, որ բոլորը սիրեն, հույս ունեմ, որ հավանողներ այնուամենայնիվ կլինեն։ Ու իմ մեդիտացիները ձեր կյանքում դրական փոփոխություններ կբերեն ☺️
Շուտով ավելի մանրամասն կգրեմ թե ինչեր եմ պատրաստում ձեր համար։
⚡Աուդիո մեդիտացիաները կկարողանաք ձեռք բերել գրելով ինձ անձնական նամակ և հավանելու ու ներքին արձագանք ունենալու դեպքում` կատարել հանգանակություն ինչքան կցանկանաք կամ գուցե չցանկանաք։ 🙏

Caption:
Hier ein Ausschnitt aus einer Audio-Meditation, die ab sofort auf ULRIKE HIRSCH TV erhältlich ist: "Meditation für das Magische Bewusstsein". 💠
Diese Audio-Meditation ist ein Live-Mitschnitt aus einer meditativen Gruppen-Mal-Session. 
Sie besteht nicht aus Worten, sondern allein aus Tönen, die ich auf meiner Hang Drum im 7/8-Takt spiele. 🎵🎶🎵
Das Besondere an diesem Stück ist der Rhythmus.
Ich spiele über eine halbe Stunde lang durchweg einen 7/8-Rhythmus, einen Rhythmus, der auf einer Siebenheit basiert. Das Zuhören und Einlassen auf diese rhythmischen Strukturen wirkt wie Sprungbrett aus dem Alltagsbewusstsein hinein ins kreative Bewusstsein. Wir schwingen uns aus dem „Erledigungsmodus“ hinein in einen freien schöpferischen Geistes- und Seelenzustand. Diese Musik ist somit wunderbar als Einstieg in den Mal-Prozess oder als Begleitmusik währenddessen geeignet sowie als Einschlaf-, Aufwach- oder Pausen-Entspannungs-Musik. ♥
Mehr über diese Meditation findet Ihr auf ULRIKE HIRSCH TV - unter www.ulrike-hirsch.tv! 📺

Caption:
Just a couple of years ago we never could've imagined that the world would be in the shape it's in. Everyone wants to do the right thing in order for things to "go back to normal". The problem is that they won't – and they can't. Expressed as the myriad of different facets in the kaleidoscope of current events, what should be undeniable to anyone despite their vantage point, is that we are living through a very important transitional period in the evolution of our collective consciousness. It's going to be a wild ride and we are just getting started.    As a man, a brother, a son, a partner, a trauma survivor, and as someone who has vowed to protect and help others, the questions have always been: "What can I do? What is within my control and how can I offer assistance to the people around me? How can I offer my medicine in a way that is useful, accessible, and easy to assimilate?" Looking for answers to these questions, I have spent the past two years structuring and refining a way to share a system to improve what I consider to be the most crucial and often overlooked aspect of healing: self-regulation. ⠀
⠀
You see, when I trace the myriad of issues that we are currently facing back to the single most important thing to focus on, what I find is not science. It's not politics. It's not media. It's not tech. What I find is the ability to modulate our emotions and our nervous system. Because a dysregulated nervous system can't bear true health, can't make the best choices, can't access intuitive wisdom, and most importantly, can't listen to a different point of view with true compassion and understanding. And if we can't all learn to come together at this pivotal point in history, things are going to get much crazier than they already are. ⠀
⠀
With this in mind, I am excited to invite you to the inaugural live course for Unmuzzle Your Power Animal, an embodiment practice that combines shamanism, meditation, breathwork, bodybuilding, yoga, tactical psychology, trauma theory, neuroscience, and emotional release techniques, presented as a powerful integrated system designed for radical self-regulation.⠀
⠀
Please check out our page! Link in bio.

Posted @with regard for • @dover_arts next broadcast Monday 9am 1st September on DCR FM | a meditative sonic treat awaits as we hand over the DAD RADIO reigns to guest host artists Edda @salander_jones and Dominic de Vere!

They present a new collaborative audio piece including field recordings from the waters around the islands of Nämdö and Harö in the Baltic Sea of the Stockholm Archipelago, Arnis on the Schlei Fjord in Schleswig-Holstein, Skeppsholmen Island in Stockholm, Knäberg in Sweden’s Värmland County, the remote British Island of Saint Helena, the Cape Peninsula in South Africa, Polzeath beach in Cornwall and a ship moving slowly through the South Atlantic Ocean.

“We are delighted to bring sounds together from our journeys on and around the world’s seas for your listening pleasure. An internal and external sonic expedition we created in August 2021, collaborating across the North Sea between Devon and Schleswig-Holstein.”

Caption:
Repost from @girlboss 😆 too good not to share. 

Pretty accurate depiction of my inner monologue scripting the latest 3 practices for @yogawakeup on Imposter Syndrome over the last month 😅

Unreasonably high expectations ✅
Perfectionism ✅
Feeling like there’s someone better to do this than me ✅
Frustrated because hard things come easy to me so when they don’t I feel like a total fraud ✅ 
Feeling shame for not getting it totally “correct” and therefore can’t ask for help ✅

Helllllooooo imposter syndrome 👋 

Turns out successful, naturally talented, very intelligent folx tend to feel this syndrome more than others and that self-doubt (in small doses) is a sign of being humble and self reflective rather than an entitled, out-of-touch twerp. 🤗 

So excited for you all to listen and practice my 3 newest On @yogawakeup - previews and discount link/free trial are all at the link in my bio.

Caption:
Participe à mon 1er LIVE sur IG!

J’ai choisi de le faire avec ma copine et collègue de longue date Lua Leo. Ensemble, et pour la premiere fois “publiquement”, nous te parlerons de notre carrière de danseuses professionnelles et de ce que ça nous a apporté par rapport à notre confiance en nous-même. Les gens me posent souvent beaucoup de questions sur ce sujet, donc là..on y va et on répond à tout!

Au menu : relation au corps, alignement, intégration de l’érotisme dans toute sa beauté et dans le quotidien. Nous aborderons aussi les points les plus difficiles, notamment comment gérer le regard (et les remarques!) des hommes, le stigma attaché a la profession, et les cotés négatifs que cette carrière peut apporter dans la vie d’une femme.

Il aura plein d’exemples et d’astuces sur comment intégrer les leçons que nous partageons dans ta vie quotidienne. Viens avec tes questions - nous prendrons le temps d’y répondre!

À propos de Lua: 
Lua (@spark.of.lua )est artiste entrepreneuse et propose une formation sur la féminité divine (@nectar.de.venus ). Elle habite depuis 10 ans en Asie, où elle divise son temps à Ubud, Bali et Goa, Inde. 
Lua et moi nous sommes rencontrées lorsque nous dansions dans un club à Shoreditch, Londres, il y a plus de 10 ans. Depuis, on fait les 400 coups à chaque fois qu’on se voit : auditions dans des clubs random à Macau,  Spa à Whistler, karaoké à deux pendant des heures (complètement sobre) à Hong Kong, couchers de soleil incroyables à Canggu (comme tu vois sur ces photos prisent l’année dernière).
Au delà du passé plutôt original que l’on partage, on est très alignée sur notre manière d’aborder la vie, la spiritualité, et nos projets professionnels. Et c’est ce que l’on partage avec toi samedi!

..
RDV : 
👉 LIVE sur IG sur ce compte 
📅 samedi de 10H30 à 11H15 (heure française) 
👩 @spark.of.lua et @anna_laurence_coaching 
👯‍♀️ partage d’expérience de danseuse pro + relation au corps
🇫🇷 En français

Comment developper ta force intérieure quand tu te sens bloqué(e)dans une situation

Caption:
I had a dream recently that I was bathing in an ocean of light. Everything around me was blurry and bioluminescent like this photo, so my dream-self knew it was a dream. With that awareness, she floated on this ocean and decided to practice yoga nidra, surrounded by and filled with the light. My dream-self slept and woke and floated and dreamt. I woke up feeling so calm, and at the same time puzzled and amazed by my dream-within-a-dream, eager to return.
.
This burst of creativity is coming to you soon in the form of a new meditation recording. To celebrate the upcoming Summer Solstice, I'll be releasing it on June 20th. The meditation will include 20 minutes of full-body guidance and relaxation, for use as a sleep aid, meditative reset, or general calming audio.
.
Sales price will increase on release day, so follow the #linkinbio to take advantage of Early Bird pricing.
.

Caption:
✨Mindful Mornings✨

Did you know that just 10 mindful minutes a day can improve your sleep, soothe anxious thoughts, and ease burnout. @jennystewartyoga new ‘Mindful Morning’ series on the on-demand library works as a guide to meditation, so that you can find a practice that works for you☺️. 

Starting your morning with meditation is a great way to start the day on the right foot. Morning meditation can help energise you, set an intention for the day, or even find peace before a busy or stressful day. Caption:
Today, on May 21, is World Meditation Day. To celebrate we’ve prepared something special for you. Check our IGTV for more!

Meditation is a big word, but the truth is that each of us can find our own way to just slow down during a busy day, stay still, check with yourself, restore focus and energy. Audio experiences, guided meditations, reflections or breathwork can help you to re-center, and put aside whatever you’re currently doing or thinking about. 

We’ve prepared a collection of some really great audio tracks which can help you focus, experience meditation in a new way, or perhaps take a first step towards mindfulness training. 

We’d like to share with you the first unique audio experience, this time it’s about pure nature sounds, without a narrative or a voiceover. It’s a recording taken by the Baltic Sea, at a beautiful beach of Jelitkowo. 

We invite you to take a slow and relaxed autumn walk at an empty beach, accompanied by waves and seagulls. The track was created for Mudita by a renown independent producer Marcin Dymiter.

Share your meditation experiences in the comments, we’d love to hear from you!
.
.
.

Caption:
Daily meditation doesn’t have to mean sitting, crossed legged chanting Om! To celebrate World Meditation Day we wanted to share with you @jennystewartyoga walking meditation audio. 

Walking meditation is an active practice that requires you to be consciously aware and moving in the environment rather than sitting down with your eyes closed💚. It’s a simple form of meditation that can be particularly valuable for beginners or anyone who prefers a more active form of this practice. Mindful walking can lead to a unique set of benefits compared with its seated counterpart, which include:

✨Connecting you with your environment 
✨Provides a sense of perspective
✨It helps connect you to the present moment
✨Getting a greater understanding of your body
✨It slows you down

Simply pop your headphones in, dress-up warm, try not to get blown away 😱, and give this audio meditation a go🙌🏻! 

If you like this, you’ll be pleased to know that next month we will be launching @jennystewartyoga Mindful Morning Series on the Online Studio. This new series will work as guide to meditation, so that you can find a practice that works for you.

🧘‍♀️🧘 Heute ist WORLD MEDITATION DAY. 🧘‍♀️🧘

Oh wie dankbar bin ich für diese wunderbare Art und Weise mich jeden Morgen mit mir selbst zu verbinden. Meine Gefühle und Gedanken klarer werden zu lassen. Mich in meinem Körper wirklich spüren zu können und praktisch als Zaungast zu beobachten, welche Impulse gerade in mir lebendig sind. Für mich ein ganz perfekter Start in den neuen Tag.

Die MEDITATION hat mein Leben verändert! Sie tut es noch immer, jeden Tag ein kleines Stückchen mehr. Wenn du auch Lust hast, auszuprobieren, was die Meditation für dich tun kann, lade dir mein kostenfreies Meditation Bundle für Mamas runter, ab heute für dich als Geschenk zum World Meditation Day. Den Link findest du im Linktree.

Fühl dich gedrückt und hab' einen wunderbaren Tag! 🌻💜

Did you know that today is World Meditation Day?

It took me a very long time to appreciate the wonder that is Meditation (Dhyana) my mind was ALWAYS busy, it would never ever stop! Some were nice thoughts but more often that not they were self-sabotaging. Meditation didn't come naturally for me, I was always thinking about my to-do lists, what I was having for dinner, the noises in the background, that itch that I needed to scratch and then the sitting still which was so excruciating. Not to mention the insects that would land on me! Trust me, meditation does not have to be like this.

If you haven't already taken me up on my free relaxing audio meditation why not give it a go today. If you already have (thank you!), I have added another one for you to have a listen too, this one is an energising one.

Choose which ever suits your mood right now or whenever is convenient to you.

I'd love if you could have a listen and let me know what you think. The link is in my bio.

Naomi ✨

Feeling Strong and Confident exercise offers a way to deeply reconnect. 🧠🧘‍♀

Sitting in a comfortable posture, close the eyes and take a few deep breaths through the nostrils. 👀👃

When you finish this practice, you may try writing about your experience. 📝 Writing after this exercise gives you a crystallized look at yourself as the strong you, and can help clarify how you are able to handle painful experiences.

Enjoy this deeply reconnection with yourself on The Silva Method Ireland YouTube.

What do you do to feel strong and confident every day?

Caption:
Geführte Meditationen - zum genau dann Anhören, wenn du sie brauchst. Wieder und wieder zum Durchatmen oder Spazieren, tags oder nachts, ganz egal. Jetzt auf Spotify. 🎶🧘🧘🏼‍♀️

Mein gemeinsames Projekt mit @onlysoul_retreats ist nun online und ich bin ganz glücklich, es dir vorstellen zu können. 

➡️Du findest ab sofort bei Spotify (Link in Bio) verschiedene geführte Meditationen. 
Gerade, wenn du neu in dem Feld bist, kann es hilfreich sein, eine achtsame Anleitung zu erhalten. 

Meditation hat wissenschaftlich bewiesen so herrliche Effekte wie beispielsweise:
- Förderung der Konzentrationsfähigkeit
- Reduktion von Stress
- Wahrnehmung deiner inneren Bedürfnisse, deines Körpers
- Mehr spüren
- Förderung von Resilizenz

Ich finde es ganz wunderbar, mehr Menschen an dem heilsamen und positiv öffnenden Prozess der Meditation teilhaben zu lassen - daher habe ich dieses Projekt mit @onlysoul_retreats angestoßen. 

Probiere dich gerne mal aus, auch wenn du noch nie meditiert hast. Die bisherigen Meditationen sind bewusst kürzer und für Anfänger*innen geeignet. 

Lass uns gerne Feedback da und vor allem liebend gern auch Wünsche für Themen - denn ein „Produkt“ ist besonders gut, wenn es die Bedürfnisse der Zielgruppe widerspiegelt. 😊

Und nicht zu vergessen: Ein großes Dankeschön auch an David Quaas aka @dekumusik für die speziell für diesen Zweck komponierten Hintergrundsounds - es ist schön zu wissen, dass es dadurch was ganz individuelles ist.

Caption:
Have you ever fancied giving meditation a try but don't know where to start? Why not let me show you how from the comfort of your own home or office at a time that suits you (no catch - I promise).

Meditation is something everyone can do to improve their mental and emotional health.

Some of the benefits of meditation can include:
💚 - reduces stress and anxiety
💚 - promotes emotional health
💚 - enhances self-awareness 
💚 - increases your attention span
💚 - improved sleep (it may even make you fall asleep)

One day I'll tell you the stories of how I learnt to meditate the hard way, it was not a smooth road, but from personal experience be kind to yourself.

If you like this meditation why not share it with a friend and see if they enjoy it too. Please do let me know if you liked it and how it made you feel. If you fancy feel free to sign up to my mailing list for more treats.

Link to the meditation is in my Bio.

Enjoy the rest of your Bank Holiday.

Naomi ✨

Caption:
✨Make the most of the lighter mornings and try a walking meditation✨

This week as part of our 30 day ‘Revive Your Mornings’ challenge were encouraging our members to make the most of the lighter mornings and try a walking meditation🙌🏻. Walking meditation is an active practice that requires you to be consciously aware and moving in the environment rather than sitting down with your eyes closed. It’s a simple form of meditation that can be particularly valuable for beginners or anyone who prefers a more active form of this practice💕. 

But why is it valuable to add a walking meditation to your morning routine🤔?

1.It Provides a Sense of Perspective - Taking a walk outdoors can break you out of a mental fog
2.It Helps You Connect to the Present Moment - As you walk and become increasingly aware, the mind grows quieter.
3.It Helps You Get to Know Your Body💕

Mindful walking is about taking your time, all the time you need. Remember, it isn’t about how fast you go, but how deeply you can feel. To support our members, @jennystewartyoga has recorded a 10 minute walking meditation. Give yourself a moment to just be. Let’s not miss all the beauty that surrounds us and remember the wander of this journey we call life.

Didn’t take part, don’t worry you can join the Online Studio and start the challenge at anytime - it’s full of daily tips, advice, challenges, exclusive breakfast recipes and classes best completed in the morning🌞! 

PLUS coming soon on the Online Studio….Power-UP May💥!

There are a lot of myths around hypnosis. 

A trained hypnotist or hypnotherapist induces a state of intense concentration or focused attention. This is a guided process with verbal cues and repetition. The state you enter may appear similar to sleep in many ways. 

❌You are ALWAYS fully aware of what is going on. 

❌You DO NOT lose control over your behaviour while under hypnosis.

❌You remain aware of and remember what happens during hypnosis.

People typically describe the feeling of being hypnotised as being in a calm, physically, and mentally relaxed state. In this state, you are able to focus deeply on what you are thinking about.

Hypnotherapy is particularly good for depression to enhance an overall sense of well-being, lift mood, and boost feelings of hopefulness.

I am a trained Clinical Hypnotherapist and in my online programs, I create audio meditations, to compliment the written work, which you can listen to at any time during the day, before you fall asleep and whilst asleep. 
 
These audio meditations will offer suggestions to your subconscious mind to help you to think more positively and uplift your sense of happiness and wellbeing.

Please note, at NO time listening to these audio meditations will you run around the room like a chicken clucking!!! 😂😂🤣

Caption:
The Loneliness update includes three new guided audio practices covering the topic of Loneliness. Each practice has been written and recorded in-house with the intention of empowering listeners to better understand what the sensation of loneliness means, what it can teach us, and how to heal + make peace with it.

• Loneliness - Accepting our emotions without fear or judgement.

• Loneliness - Learning from the sensation of loneliness.

• Loneliness - Accepting our interdependence.

Each of these practices has an extended version that takes a deeper look into the physiology of our emotions in connection to loneliness.

Caption:
Jipiii!!! Ich freue mich sehr heute mit euch meine erste Audio-Entspannung zu teilen!! Als kleines Ostergeschenk habe ich für euch Yoga Nirda aufgenommen.
Yoga Nirda, auch "der Schlaf des Yogi" genannt, ist eine Yoga-Technik, die durch tiefe Entspannung den Zugang zu tieferen Bewusstseinsschichten ermöglicht. Es ist eine systematische Methode, um vollkommene mentale, emotionale und physische Entspannung herbeizuführen. Yoga Nidra kann dir helfen, besser zu entspannen, Stress zu reduzieren, und kann bei vielen Beschwerden lindernd wirken.
Wann immer du dich gestresst fühlst nutze meine Aufzeichnung und komme zurück in einen ruhigen ausgeglichenen Zustand. Am besten wirkt die Methode, wenn du Yoga Nidra regelmäßig anwendest. Du wirst merken, dass du dich immer schneller auf die Entspannung einlassen kannst und tiefer entspannst. 

Vielen Dank an @kid_copper für die Zusammenarbeit. 

Ich wünsche euch eine schöne Osterzeit! 🌷🌞🦋

Caption:
💛 Neuer Podcast: Resonanzen 💛

Wie du unangenehme Trigger in wundervolle Geschenke für dich verwandeln kannst

Ihr Lieben, 💛

diese Podcastfolge ist mal wieder aufgrund einer Frage in unserer Workshop-Facebookgruppe entstanden, in der es darum geht, woran du erkennst, ob ein Thema, zu dem du Resonanz hast, das dich also antriggert, eigentlich wirklich deins ist, oder ob du da nur das Thema von jemand anderen wahrnimmst.

Tatsächlich hat alles, wozu du Resonanz hast, etwas mit einem Muster in dir zu tun – das ist bei negativen Triggern genauso der Fall, wie bei allem, was dich in positiver Weise berührt. 

Daher ist es super wertvoll für dich, wenn dich etwas unangenehm antriggert, zu schauen, was das tatsächlich in dir auslöst, welche Gedanken, Überzeugungen, Emotionen, Erinnerungen und Ähnliches du damit verbindest, damit du im wahrsten Sinne des Wortes Licht in die Sache bringen kannst und dieses beengende Muster in dir erhellen kannst. Denn das bringt sehr viel mehr Freiheit in dein Leben.

Genau das machen wir dann in der Meditation der heutigen Folge, damit du deine unangenehmen Trigger in wundervolle Geschenke für dich verwandeln kannst.

Ich wünsche dir ganz viel Freude und neue Freiheit! 🤗

Liebe liebe Grüße! 💛
Dagmar

Caption:
I’m so happy! The reviews for my audio meditation came in! 

These feedbacks are exactly WHY I recorded the meditation in the first place and it is what inspired the script for Stepping Into Your Greatness meditation. 

[If you haven’t downloaded yet, it’s on my website www.intuitwithjessie.com]

I was often asked where did I learn and how do I know how to meditate? 

In this lifetime, my first experience was taught by a Buddhist monk in a temple. It was just me and the cement floor, no fan, in the tropical weather for one hot hour. First time, and I sat through it 60 minutes when everyone else had already left the room. He said I’ve done this before. 

10 years later, I started receiving visions of myself. 

Many lifetimes ago, I was a male monk in Tibet in the 1600 AD. I saw myself as a 5’2” small framed, dark skin, very skinny young man who came out of the monastery to explore enlightenment on his own. Once a week, he will take a few hours walk to a nearby village town to ask for food and then retrieve back the small cave up in the mountain and meditate. In winter times, he meditated there the whole of 4 months without food and kept his body warm through the frigid temperature. 

I didn’t know surviving the winter months with a robe was possible until recently, I chanced upon a Youtube documentary of monks using a yoga technique to enter a state of deep meditation and significantly raise their body heat known as ‘g Tum-mo’. 

I was shocked! Yes, I still get shocked with my own ability sometimes. 

And also, now I know why I sweat when I meditate. 

This is how the knowledge and techniques of meditation came naturally to me. It helps when I learn more and I get to remember how I did it in the psat. As I learned, I tweaked it to our modern lifestyle so that it is easier to ‘digest’. 

My goal is that everyone experience some kind of peace in a day, even if it’s just 10 minutes — You’ll be much better off. 

Have you tried the audio meditation? Would love to hear your thought. 

[Download at www.intuitiwithjessie.com]

DIE INNERE STILLE HÜTEN • und den eigenen Rhythmus spüren
•
Wenn es dir zwischendurch zu wirr wird da draußen - oder da drinnen, im eigenen Kopf - und du gefühlt völlig aus dem Takt gekommen bist: take a BREATHER!

Der Atem ist uns ein so verlässlicher GRUNDRHYTHMUS, ein uns eigener, uns entsprechender, dass wir ihn, bewusst geführt, als pace maker nutzen können, um zu unserem natürlichen Rhythmus zurückzukehren. Und dann wird er zu einer Meditation.

•
Das sind 20 Minuten, die deine tägliche Morgen- oder Abendmeditation werden können. Oder auch deine spezielle Auszeit in dichten Zeiten. Auf jeden Fall ein Anker, der dir immer zur Verfügung steht, wenn du ihn brauchst.

Caption:
How My Meditation Journey Started
.
My meditation journey started when I wholeheartedly fell involve with practicing yoga three years ago, although it has always been present in my life. Remembering myself as a child staying at my grandparents’ house, my grandmother would practice yoga every morning. She had a thick book about yoga and meditation, and I would flick through the pages, curiously observing each picture of all the different poses whilst my grandmother would lay in Savasana pose, kindly encouraging for silence if I began to ask too many questions. Now I understand! Yoga and meditation have allowed me to grow and transform not only my body but my thoughts and habits in ways that I did not think possible. During this time, I began to explore a wide array of therapeutic sessions ranging from Tibetan healing bowls, aromatherapy, breath-work, and crystal meditations. Soon after, I decided to open up my own platform focused on meditation and mindfulness for others to join along with me to simply slow down their mind. I strongly believe pure happiness is achieved when you stop waiting for life to begin and start making the most of the moment you are in. Taking one day at a time.

Caption:
Guided Mindfulness Meditation Audio Lecture
.
This practice guides you to pay particularly close attention to the sensations of the breath. Observing the very start of an inhale and following all the way to the very end of an exhale. This practice allows you not only to acknowledge your object of focus — the breath —, but also the entire process of it. This mindfulness meditation encourages you to adapt the skill of conscious awareness — we simply stay with what is. You will learn how to remain aware of when you drift away and get caught in thoughts that are anywhere but right here and right now. It is in our natural nature to grab at thoughts, but when you will get into a habit of mindful awareness, you will be able to observe your thoughts and feelings without judging them. You will be guided into the present space, examining the state of your body whilst maintaining your attention on the breath.
.

Caption:
What is meditation?
.
There are different ways to meditate, and since it's such a personal practice, there are probably more than any of us know about. There are a couple that is usually focused on heavily in scientific research, though. These are focused-attention, or mindful meditation, where you focus on one specific thing: your breathing, a sensation in your body, or a particular object outside of you. The point of this type of meditation is to focus intensely on one topic and continually bring your attention back to that focal point when it wanders.
The other type of meditation that's often used in research is open-monitoring meditation. This is where you pay attention to all of the things happening around you—you notice everything without reacting.
.

Caption:
“Things falling apart is a kind of testing and also a kind of healing.  We think the point is to pass the test or to overcome the problem, but the truth is that things don’t really get solved.  They come together and they fall apart.  Then they come together again and fall apart again.  It’s just like that.  The healing comes from letting there be room for all of this to happen:  room for grief, for relief, for misery, for joy.” -pema chodron 

In this meditation, we will create space to simply be with our human experience. I’ll mind the time, and you’ll drop into the space within.

When thoughts arise, like they often do, don’t strive to control them, but rather let them be. Label them as thinking, thinking, thinking, and return to your center.

Caption:
*NEW BLOG POST* Have you heard of Binaural Beats? It is a sound technology that can be used to help facilitate specific brain wave states.

How can a binaural beat help us hack our brain wave state? A binaural beat simply means playing two different frequencies at the same time in a different ear. Binaural beats require a stereo audio interface, typically a pair of stereo headphones. What does "stereo" mean? It simply means that there is a left and right audio channel that can play independently of each other. When listening to a binaural beat, you hear one frequency in either the left or right ear and a slightly different frequency in the other ear. Through a process called "entrainment", the brain tries to reconcile the slight difference in frequency and over time can actually begin to oscillate at the DIFFERENCE in the two frequencies. 

In the example image above, a frequency of 40 Hz is played in the left ear and a frequency of 50 Hz is played in the right. The brain hears these differences in frequency (which is 10 Hz) and wants to "reconcile" the difference by beginning to migrate it's own frequency to that difference. What is 10 Hz in brain wave states? It is the Alpha state, associated with activating the parasympathetic nervous system and relaxation!

**CHECK OUT MY BLOG FOR THE FULL ARTICLE! (Link in Bio)** I will have some binaural beat tracks coming out really soon for your listening pleasure! 

Have you listened to binaural beats? What has your experience been with them?

Mindfulness meditation encourages you to slow down, allows for deeper self-reflection, and can help you discover positive attributes about yourself. 
.

Mindfulness meditation can also lower cortisol levels — the stress hormone —which helps you feel more relaxed. 
.

Caption:
Can the work of an artist’s hands help you encounter God? I believe it can. 

Visio divina means “divine seeing” in Latin, as we gaze upon a work of art and experience God’s presence through it.

It engages the eye and the imagination. You can do it with a piece of art, religious or not, or even a leaf or landscape you discover outside. If you are visual, as so many of us are today, then visio divina can be a refreshing way to experience God.

Artist Tim Mooney says of visio divina: "It invites us to be seen, addressed, surprised, and transformed by God who is never limited or tied to any image, but speaks through them.”

Using a piece called Rainbow Hands from the book A Cloud of Outrageous Blue by Vesper Stamper, I lead a 10-minute visio divina exercise on the podcast this week. It's an amazing piece of art that may just remind you who God made you to be as a creative person.

Listen via my profile, and there's a special link to the piece in the shownotes.

Caption:
Seriously Leute… ich hatte früher so Angst vor der Stille. Es war ungewohnt. Es war anders. Anfangs dachte ich es sei langweilig. Now I know: die Stille ist niemals leer. Sie ist voller Antworten. She is the key to success. Der Weg zu allem Großen geht durch die Stille...⁣
⁣
Durch das Meditieren in Stille habe ich die Angst vor der Stille in innere Kraft und Integrität verwandeln können. Denn in der Stille begegnest du deiner Wahrheit. Momente der puren Klarheit. Frieden in dir. Vergebung. Das Gefühl von ONENESS. Tiefe Verbundenheit zu dir und deiner Seele. Ich wäre niemals da, wo ich jetzt bin ohne Meditation in Stille. Es scheint so simpel und doch so herausfordernd. Denn es bringt uns niemand bei. Und weil die Stille so unglaublich viel in meinem Leben verändert hat, supporte ich dich mit »Meditate with Loa« dabei, die Stille step by step lieben zu lernen und das größte Geschenk dieser Welt zu erhalten: die Verbindung zu deiner Wahrheit. In 3 Tagen geht's endlich los!!⁣
⁣
Und jetzt mal ganz ehrlich: Wie stehst du zum Thema Stille? Wie sind deine Gefühle und Gedanken zur Stille? Let’s talk about silence in the comments, friends 👇🏼

💚Уж не знаю, почему я не выложила их сразу, но, значит, всему своё время) Вот, держите сейчас - подборочка визуальных и звуковых медитативов. Из очень секретного и заряженного энергией места🌝
Помню, какая наполненная я приехала после поездки оттуда💫
Сейчас, в это межсезонье, ведущее в осень, не помешает напитаться лёгкостью и чистотой этих волшебных естественных потоков кристальной живой воды💙
.
Внимание: для правильного эффекта нужно 
1) включить звук🔈
2)немного замедлиться💭
3)замедитировать☯️
и 4)enjoy!😉🤗✨
.
.

Are you as wealthy and successful as you'd like to be?  Whether you realise it or not, your level of wealth and success reflects exactly what you believe you deserve.

In this lively discussion with her audience, Louise explains how we can use our mind power to attract anything we want into our lives—more money, a rewarding career, fulfilling relationships, and more fun!
